Programming is just about learning new tricks, practicing them and becoming so familiar that they come naturally.
To improve your logical skills, you can learn discrete mathematics, algorithms etc.
For Discrete Mathematics, this is a great lecture series:
http://archive.org/details/arsdi...

For Algorithm, lecture series by MIT is great
http://video.google.com/videopla...

Also, there are lots of online programming sites where you can practice problems, take part in programming contest and interact with other programmers.
Few such sites are: 
codejam
http://www.codechef.com/
http://projecteuler.net/
http://www.topcoder.com/
https://www.interviewstreet.com/
http://codeforces.com/
https://lembra.wordpress.com/category/java/
http://gibbon.co
